venv/
    __pycache__/
    db.sqlite3
    node_modules/
    .DS_Store
    ```
3.  **Commit your work:**
    
```bash
    git add .
    git commit -m "Initial commit: Full stack app with AI logic"
    ```

---

## Milestone 8: Dockerizing the App (Part 2)

Docker wraps your app in a "container" so it has everything it needs to run. We need three main files in your root folder (`edupredict_project`).

### 1. `Dockerfile` (for the Backend)
Create a file named `Dockerfile` (no extension) in the root:
```dockerfile
FROM python:3.10
WORKDIR /app
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt
COPY . .
CMD ["python", "manage.py", "runserver", "0.0.0.0:8000"]